<section>
  <h2 id="spacing-unit-widths">Spacing Unit Widths</h2>
  <p>
    Width classes based on Foundation CSS spacing units. These are calculated using
    <code>$su-step</code> (84px at default font size) and provide consistent sizing across your
    design system.
  </p>

  <aside class="bg-light-025 p4 br-md mb4">
    <h4>About Spacing Unit Widths</h4>
    <p class="mb2">
      Spacing unit widths are based on <code>$su-full</code> (1008px) divided by 12, creating a
      12-column grid system. Each <code>$su-step</code> equals approximately 84px at the default
      font size.
    </p>
    <p>
      These widths automatically adjust with font size changes, maintaining proportional
      relationships across different screen sizes.
    </p>
  </aside>

